   "source": [
    "## 13. Interpreting Statistical Significance in Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "A significant regression result implies:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Changes in the predictor variable are systematically associated with changes in the response variable.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, significance alone does NOT imply:\n",
    "- Causality\n",
    "- Strong predictive accuracy\n",
    "- Practical importance\n",
    "\n",
    "This distinction is **extremely important** in applied analytics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate significance vs practical importance\n",
    "np.random.seed(123)\n",
    "n_large = 10000\n",
    "X_large = np.random.uniform(0, 1, n_large)\n",
    "Y_large = 100 + 0.05 * X_large + np.random.normal(0, 1, n_large)\n",
    "\n",
    "model_large = sm.OLS(Y_large, sm.add_constant(X_large)).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Example: Statistical Significance WITHOUT Practical Importance\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 65)\n",
    "print(f\"Sample size: {n_large}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Estimated slope: {model_large.params[1]:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-value: {model_large.pvalues[1]:.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Interpretation: A 1-unit increase in X is associated with a {model_large.params[1]:.4f}-unit change in Y\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nIs this statistically significant? {'YES' if model_large.pvalues[1] < 0.05 else 'NO'}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Is this practically meaningful? Probably NOT (very small effect size)\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nR-squared: {model_large.rsquared:.4f} (very low explanatory power)\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nMoral: Statistical significance + Large sample size = Easy to find tiny effects\")\n",
    "print(\"Always consider practical significance alongside statistical significance!\")"
