    "## 19. R-Squared: Measuring Model Fit\n",
    "\n",
    "R-squared ($R^2$) measures the **proportion of variance explained** by the model.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$R^2 = 1 - \\frac{\\text{SS}_{\\text{res}}}{\\text{SS}_{\\text{total}}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- $\\text{SS}_{\\text{res}} = \\sum(y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2$ (unexplained variance)\n",
    "- $\\text{SS}_{\\text{total}} = \\sum(y_i - \\bar{y})^2$ (total variance)\n",
    "\n",
    "$R^2$ ranges from 0 to 1:\n",
    "- $R^2 = 0$: Model explains nothing\n",
    "- $R^2 = 1$: Perfect fit\n",
    "\n",
    "**Warning:** Adding more predictors always increases $R^2$ (adjusted $R^2$ penalizes complexity)."
   ]
  },
